# RAG-LLM-API-Pipeline

A fully  local GPU poor, multimodal Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) system powered by open-source local LLMs. This pipeline is designed for operational technology environments to provide AI-assisted access to technical knowledge, manuals, and historical data â€” securely and offline, at min cost.

---

## âœ… Key Features

- ğŸ” Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) using FAISS + SentenceTransformers
- ğŸ§  Query handling via a local, open-source Large Language Model (LLM)
- ğŸ“„ Supports multiple input formats:
  - PDFs
  - Plain text files
  - Images (OCR via Tesseract)
  - Audio files (`.wav`, `.flac`, `.aiff`)
  - Videos (`.mp4` with audio extraction)
- ğŸ’» Interfaces:
  - Command Line Interface (CLI)
  - Local REST API (FastAPI)
- ğŸ› ï¸ Asset definition via YAML configuration
- ğŸ” Works in fully local environments after setup

âœ… Works locally, GPU/CPU-friendly with configurable precision  
âœ… CLI, API and simple web UI included


